Body: To invest successfully, make sure the project is trustworthy. Crypto market is a minefield of scam projects. Scam is a project where you end up with no benefits and no money. How to detect it? Mind the four T-s:  üïµÔ∏è Theme. Is the concept behind the project viable and economically feasible? Do they really need blockchain? Key peers, target audience volume, goal complexity ‚Äî assess everything. Read the description, Roadmap and White Paper. üïµÔ∏è Tech. Is the Roadmap detailed enough? Any working prototype or ready product? Check out the project‚Äôs source code on Github and technical description in the White Paper. üïµÔ∏è Team. The best idea can be ruined by an inept team. Find out the background of leaders, developers and marketers, assess their teamplay and experience as entrepreneurs. Read the publications by reputable media outlets and comments by industry experts who assess the project favourably. üïµÔ∏è Token. What‚Äôs the total number of tokens? What‚Äôs their name and legal status? What's going to drive their value? The White Paper shall give all the answers.  If you are happy with all the four T-s, then the project is likely to be worth investing. However, do remember that no one can provide a 100% guarantee, better double-check the information.

Title: [ANN] [Token Sale] mytime - We Turn Time Into Cryptocurrency
Body: Loyalty programs prompt people to stockpile points and make new purchases. This tool is supposed to work well, and hence is favored by 70% of companies. So far, people end up collecting and losing numerous cards, each accepted by one or two stores.  Now fancy, there‚Äôs a global loyalty program enabling you to earn and spend points at a variety of companies, stores, and services. ‚ÄòHey, what's the point for business owners to share their customers?‚Äô you would ask. And here comes a solution ‚Äî the mytime platform caters to the needs of both parties.  Businesses will be able to reward customers with cryptocoins, while customers may choose to spend coins at other stores, or change for fiat money. The growing number of services joining the loyalty program, will help companies enhance monetization opportunities for their audiences. On top of that, companies can collect, store and sell user behavior data, be it active users or quitters. As a result, the value of each customer goes up. And the risk of ‚Äòsharing the audience‚Äô is no longer perceived as such, becoming a monetization opportunity.

Author: MyTimeCoin
Title: [ANN] [Token Sale] mytime - We Turn Time Into Cryptocurrency
Body: Thanks! The protocol will be based on four main principles: ‚Ä¢ A platform participant may pay for the time spent by another participant using MYTC. Time is confirmed by payment, with entries made into the public ledger. The cost of time will be further determined based on these entries. ‚Ä¢ A participant‚Äôs emission share is proportionate to the amount of MYTC it uses to confirm the time invested by other participants. ‚Ä¢ The reputation of a platform participant is derived from their transaction history recorded in the ledger. ‚Ä¢ Conflicts arising from selling one and the same time interval to different participants are resolved at the protocol level.  You can read more in our whitepaper: https://mytimecoin.github.io/whitepaper/whitepaper_en.pdf

Author: MyTimeCoin
Title: [ANN] [Token Sale] mytime - We Turn Time Into Cryptocurrency
Body: Companies collecting and selling data (SSP, DSP)  Today, companies have learned to make the most of customer data in personalizing offers, targeting, and boosting loyalty. A most compelling tool here is programmatic buying ‚Äî an automated auction-based system for targeted ads.  Programmatic operates on platforms representing interests of advertisers (DSP, demand selling platform) and site owners (SSP, supply selling platform). Both make use of DMP (data management platform) which allows storing, processing and segmenting data.  Companies gathering and supplying data: ‚Ä¢ Raw data suppliers ‚Äî sell raw data (for instance, histories of visits and likes). ‚Ä¢ Processed data suppliers ‚Äî buy data from RDA, process it and get look-a-like segments. ‚Ä¢ Data exchange ‚Äî provide their platform for data transmission to customers.  With mytime companies will be able to maximize the efficiency of data. Indeed, there‚Äôs no information so valuable as how people spend their time. Businesses will record data on user activities on their services in a blockchain, and then sell this information to other companies.

Title: [ANN] [Token Sale] mytime - We Turn Time Into Cryptocurrency
Body: Accumulation of time-recording transactions in the blockchain will lead to user history building up step by step, and that will form the participants‚Äô transaction profiles. The entire history of user interaction with other platform participants will be recorded in the blockchain, user identity depersonalised. It will be transparent and easily accessible. The participants‚Äô transaction profiles will form user reputation. It will enable the service providers to search for the required audience by setting certain parameters, for look-alike targeting.  Quote from: Roofer111 on December 22, 2017, 07:22:09 AM And how will you protect the data you get? You will basically know exactly what your users do  We aren't creating any software for unauthorised tracking of people's time for an operating system. Instead, we're creating a protocol describing how a service provider makes user time entries into a blockchain. Say, an iOS game can simply track a player's interaction time and broadcast a transaction into the network. Time is tracked by the service itself making use of the module embedded in its application.

Author: MyTimeCoin
Title: [ANN] [Token Sale] mytime - We Turn Time Into Cryptocurrency
Body: Big Data retrospect  The term Big Data popped up a while ago, but as a phenomenon it had existed before the Common Era. At that time it was about calculation, analysis and structuring of data in libraries and troops. With the growing amount of information, the processes were getting more complex.  The first Big Data revolution at the start of the 19th century gave rise to the era of analog data storage. It became possible to preserve sounds and images on magnetic tapes, aside from transferring to paper.  The 20th century marks a shift from analog to digital media: 1956 ‚Äî IBM introduces the first hard disk drive, weighing about 1 ton. 1982 ‚Äî Sony and Philips release the first digital optical disc. 1989 ‚Äî the term Data Mining is coined.  Today‚Äôs world sees at least a 30% annual growth in information volumes. According to Cisco, in 2019 the annual global traffic will reach two zettabytes.  mytime will record and store Big Data on a decentralized network. Each service will have access to its user data in desensitized format. Businesses will be able to sell this data and use it for promotion campaign targeting.

Title: [ANN] [Token Sale] mytime - We Turn Time Into Cryptocurrency
Body: Thanks for asking! The idea is pretty simple yet effective. First, a company (service) integrates with our platform and buys MYTC for fiat money. Then, it encourages users to spend time on its service in exchange for MYTC. Conditions for rewards will be set using smart-contracts for maximum clarity and transparency. There will be two blockchains, Time and Money. The first one will keep records of time spent by users on services. The second one will store records of transactions between platform participants.

Title: [ANN] [Token Sale] mytime - We Turn Time Into Cryptocurrency
Body: mytime is not a standalone product, but a platform with its own infrastructure to integrate with various services. The platform will be open-source, so that developers could use it in their projects. Service providers will be integrated via dedicated tools we are now developing:  ‚Äî Platform API: a software interface for interaction with the mytime platform. ‚Äî Exchange API: a software interface for integration with cryptocurrency exchanges and trading MYTC for other cryptocurrencies. ‚Äî Basic application: a MYTC wallet and a marketplace of services integrated with the mytime platform.  mytime‚Äôs primary function is to let service providers validate users‚Äô time and actions. It can be done manually and automatically, using a third-party solution.

Author: MyTimeCoin
Title: [ANN] [Token Sale] mytime - We Turn Time Into Cryptocurrency
Body: Functions of the Time and Money blockchains  Our mytime platform will use two interconnected blockchains ‚Äî Time –∏ Money.  The first one will keep records of user time spent on a service (for example, from 10:25 till 10:40). Based on these records users will be rewarded with MYTC as described in smart contracts.  Money is a ledger of MYTC transactions between the platform participants. Both blockchains are being developed by our team with an eye to the best practices of today ‚Äî Cardano, Plasma, EOS, and Graphene.  The interconnected functioning of two blockchains is a cornerstone of our platform.

Author: MyTimeCoin
Title: [ANN] [Token Sale] mytime - We Turn Time Into Cryptocurrency
Body: Blockchain & Bitcoin Conference Malta  Much has been said about mytime from the user perspective, but what is mytime for businesses?  Our blockchain platform enables businesses to create a robust loyalty program, rewarding customers with cryptocurrency for their time. Moreover, mytime serves as a marketplace where businesses will sell customer behaviour data.  How will it work? While a person gets coins for the time spent on a service, the service accumulates information about this person‚Äôs behaviour and records it in the blockchain. Businesses may buy and sell the accumulated data to each other.  This is an opportunity for businesses to develop a customer-tailored approach, both to attract and retain the audience.  More details will be given by our co-founder Alexander Zelenshikov at tomorrow‚Äôs Blockchain & Bitcoin Conference, taking place in Malta https://malta.blockchainconf.world/en. Come talk to us!

Author: MyTimeCoin
Title: [ANN] [Token Sale] mytime - We Turn Time Into Cryptocurrency
Body: Armen Gulinyan  We continue introducing the founders of mytime. Armen Gulinyan ‚Äî our Chief Business Officer.  Armen is a founder of Pladform and CEO of Ruform (Pladform+Rutube), a video content distribution company. Ruform shares 25% of Russia‚Äôs video adverts market: the platform boasts over 10 billion video ad impressions a year. Also, Ruform is a major partner of vk.com.  We are greatly proud of our team, where everyone‚Äôs experience and expertise is unique.

Author: MyTimeCoin
Title: [ANN] [Token Sale] mytime - We Turn Time Into Cryptocurrency
Body: No Time Tracking  How are we going to track user time spent on services, check their activity and tell people from bots? We aren‚Äôt going to in any way, and this is our basic position.  mytime is a platform recording payments made for the elapsed time. We‚Äôre creating a universal LTV tool to let businesses reward customers for their time.  As for time verification, we leave it up to services. There‚Äôre already a great many tools devised to record user time, track their activity and raise fraud alerts. We‚Äôd rather leave it to professionals and focus on what we can do well and like ‚Äî developing a new approach to loyalty.

Author: MyTimeCoin
Title: [ANN] [Token Sale] mytime - We Turn Time Into Cryptocurrency
Body: Time is Money  Your every second is unlikely to earn you income if spent on anything, but work. Time is the most valuable resource convertible into tangible benefits through labour.  A salary of $1000 and 160 working hours a month gives an hourly rate of nearly $6. In the U.S. this figure averages to $31, in Germany - $24, in China - $2.6.  What about monetizing the remaining 560 hours?  mytime offers an opportunity to earn cryptocurrency in your leisure activity, outside of work. After our platform is integrated with various services you‚Äôll be able to earn as much as you use your time: at work, on your way home, having meals. You‚Äôll be able to receive coins for watching videos on a streaming service. Or get MYTC for taking an online educational course. Or get paid in cryptocurrency by game publishers for every minute spent in a game. You‚Äôve got it right - you‚Äôll be able to monetize your leisure time! Well yes, because time is never enough, same as money.

Author: MyTimeCoin
Title: [ANN] [Token Sale] mytime - We Turn Time Into Cryptocurrency
Body: Mytime‚Äôs basic function is to let companies pay users for the exact amount of time spent on their services. Reading an article, watching a video or riding a taxi ‚Äî get your coins for every second. But it‚Äôs just the tip of the iceberg.  Any company may set its own conditions and agree with users on buying their future time. How it works? A service provider buys MYTC and describes the conditions for its user in a smart contract. For instance, to spend 30 minutes a day on its service over the course of a week. A user who meets the conditions receives the agreed amount of MYTC. This way a user is motivated to use the service regularly. And a company benefits anyway ‚Äî even if forgotten by a user at some point.  mytime is both a useful and beneficial tool for all!

Author: MyTimeCoin
Title: [ANN] [Token Sale] mytime - We Turn Time Into Cryptocurrency
Body: How are you going to record user time spent on different services? How are you going to track bots? These are the questions we are frequently asked at meetings and conferences. To make it clear, we have drawn up a disclaimer for you:  *We do not propose any ready-made economic models for businesses. We are developing a tool for businesses to increase the loyalty and LTV already now, and, ultimately - to determine the value of human time across industries. We equip businesses with new rules of the game, that allow competing for customers in the new economic dimension where time plays the lead.  *We are not going to determine the amount of time spent by people and what they were doing. This function remains with a party interested in a person‚Äôs time. Businesses have already learned how to track users‚Äô time ‚Äì there‚Äôre a lot of tools serving this purpose. What we do, is register payments made to compensate for the invested time, and use this information to build a new open economy.  *We won‚Äôt have our own bot tracking system for online services ‚Äî services have learned how to distinguish, with sufficient accuracy, bots from real people among their audience. Instead, we‚Äôre creating a reputation mechanism that will reflect, in encrypted format, how much time and on what services a person spends. Reputation will help businesses find users fitting best their interests, and pay for the time of these particular users.

Author: MyTimeCoin
Title: [ANN] [Token Sale] mytime - We Turn Time Into Cryptocurrency
Body: Hi! This is not quite true. The user doesn't need to share any data. You just use a service that is integrated with mytime platform and receive cryptocurrency for it. For example, if Netflix integrates with mytime, you will get paid for watching movies and sitcoms. The only data we get is how much time you've spent in a particular service and how much it paid you. And yes, this data is impersonal. No personal data is collected and stored by the mytime platform.  You can learn more about mytime in our whitepaper: https://mytimecoin.github.io/whitepaper/whitepaper_en.pdf
